snippet.textDisplay: No sorry, this was too predictable, uneventful and artificially put together. Instead of Warren v Liam, and Liam`s very hard to grasp idea that almost anybody but himself is to be blamed for his misery. Liam and Jordan should have been the two rivals. Jordan arriving on Liam`s territory, Liam not liking it one bit, and first mistakenly assume Sid and Juliet to be his competitors. That would at lest make sense. Why should Warren hate Liam? The two of them have barely been in the village at the same time ever - it is more odd they remember what the other looks like. And both the triangle between Brody, Liberty and Sienna, and Diane, Tony and Edward are equally weird and therefore not very interesting as SLs. And if Toby and Celeste wasn`t weird enough, Mitchell and Toby (or is the true sibling he/she now being called Celeste?) has a dad, we have to be lumbered with too. After the arrival of Tony`s dad, I am not exactly optimistic.
